quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
  95,1,"By the fig, and the olive."
  95,2,"By Mount Sinai."
  95,3,"By this city of security (Makkah).{1}",footnotes:1:1
  95,4,"Verily, We created man in the best stature (mould)."
  95,5,"Then We reduced him to the lowest of the low."
  95,6,"Save those who believe (in Islâmic Monotheism) and do righteous deeds. Then they shall have a reward without end (Paradise)."
  95,7,"Then what (or who) causes you (O disbelievers) to deny the Recompense (i.e. the Day of Resurrection)?"
  95,8,"Is not Allâh the Best of judges?"
  96,1,"Read! In the Name of your Lord Who has created (all that exists)."
  96,2,"He has created man from a clot (a piece of thick coagulated blood)."
  96,3,"Read! And your Lord is the Most Generous."
  96,4,"Who has taught (the writing) by the pen."
  96,5,"He has taught man that which he knew not."
  96,6,"Nay! Verily, man does transgress (in disbelief and evil deed)."
  96,7,"Because he considers himself self-sufficient."
  96,8,"Surely, unto your Lord is the return."
  96,9,"Have you (O Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم) seen him (i.e. Abû Jahl) who prevents"
  96,10,"A slave (Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم) when he prays?"